                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 13.242,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 81648,
                                "text": "The second case I have to announce is No. 03-526, Schriro v. Summerlin."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 13.242,
                                "stop": 18.721,
                                "byte_start": 81648,
                                "byte_stop": 103591,
                                "text": "This case is here on writ of certiorari to the Ninth Circuit Court of Appeals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 18.721,
                                "stop": 33.345,
                                "byte_start": 103591,
                                "byte_stop": 162105,
                                "text": "The petitioner Warren Summerlin was sentenced to death in 1982, 22 years ago, for the murder of Brenna Bailey in Arizona."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 33.345,
                                "stop": 40.165,
                                "byte_start": 162105,
                                "byte_stop": 189377,
                                "text": "Arizona law authorizes the death penalty if one or more aggravating factors is present."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.165,
                                "stop": 47.354,
                                "byte_start": 189377,
                                "byte_stop": 218112,
                                "text": "At the time that finding of an aggravating factor was made by a judge rather than a jury."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.354,
                                "stop": 52.314,
                                "byte_start": 218112,
                                "byte_stop": 237965,
                                "text": "The judge in Summerlin\u2019s case found two aggravating factors and sentenced him to death."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 52.314,
                                "stop": 55.368,
                                "byte_start": 237965,
                                "byte_stop": 250190,
                                "text": "That sentence was affirmed on Appeal."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 55.368,
                                "stop": 73.701,
                                "byte_start": 250190,
                                "byte_stop": 323542,
                                "text": "Nearly 20 years later, we decided in Ring v. Arizona, that Arizona\u0027s capital sentencing and procedures violated the Sixth Amendment by allowing the judge rather than the jury to find the facts essential to imposition of the death penalty."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 73.701,
                                "stop": 76.619,
                                "byte_start": 323542,
                                "byte_stop": 335245,
                                "text": "This was an application of Apprendi."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 76.619,
                                "stop": 89.213,
                                "byte_start": 335245,
                                "byte_stop": 385609,
                                "text": "The Ninth Circuit acting on Summerlin\u2019s federal habeas petition held that our decision in Ring could be applied retroactively to his case and overturned his death sentence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 89.213,
                                "stop": 94.273,
                                "byte_start": 385609,
                                "byte_stop": 405776,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the Clerk today, we reverse the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 94.273,
                                "stop": 105.656,
                                "byte_start": 405776,
                                "byte_stop": 451333,
                                "text": "When a decision of this Court results in a new rule, that rule applies to convictions that are already final only in certain limited circumstances."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.656,
                                "stop": 110.405,
                                "byte_start": 451333,
                                "byte_stop": 470350,
                                "text": "New substantive rules generally apply retroactive."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 110.405,
                                "stop": 127,
                                "byte_start": 470350,
                                "byte_stop": 536701,
                                "text": "New procedural rules, on the other hand, apply retroactively only, we have said, if they qualify as watershed rules of criminal procedure implicating the fundamental fairness and accuracy of the criminal proceeding."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 127,
                                "stop": 139.806,
                                "byte_start": 536701,
                                "byte_stop": 587901,
                                "text": "That a new procedural rule is fundamental in some abstract sense is not enough, the rule must be one without which the likelihood of an accurate conviction is seriously diminished."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 139.806,
                                "stop": 157.404,
                                "byte_start": 587901,
                                "byte_stop": 658328,
                                "text": "We conclude that Ring\u2019s holding is properly classified as procedural, it did not alter the range of conduct or the class of persons subject to the death penalty in Arizona, but only the method of determining whether the defendant engaged in the criminal conduct."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.404,
                                "stop": 177.894,
                                "byte_start": 658328,
                                "byte_stop": 740352,
                                "text": "We further conclude that Ring did not announce a watershed rule of criminal procedure, even though the right to jury trial is fundamental under our constitution, we cannot confidently say the judicial factfinding, as opposed to jury factfinding seriously diminishes accuracy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 177.894,
                                "stop": 196.758,
                                "byte_start": 740352,
                                "byte_stop": 815794,
                                "text": "It is a mode of finding the facts used in many other countries of the world, and as I indicated in announcing the prior case, the principal purpose of jury trial in the American system is not accuracy, but assurance of control by the people."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 196.758,
                                "stop": 202.185,
                                "byte_start": 815794,
                                "byte_stop": 837423,
                                "text": "Accordingly, we reverse the judgment of the Ninth Circuit and remand the case for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 202.185,
                                "stop": 225.324,
                                "byte_start": 837423,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Breyer has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justices Stevens, Souter, and Ginsburg joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
